description:
/usr/lib64/pkgconfig/libmongoc-1.0.pc contains:
{noformat}
Libs: -L${libdir} -lmongoc-1.0 -lsasl2  -lssl -lcrypto  -lrt -lresolv -lz  -lsnappy 
{noformat}
But applications linked against libmongoc probably don't need these library.

Reported as https://bugzilla.redhat.com/1560611

Evergreen [compiles mongo-c-driver with -Werror|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-c-driver/blob/r1.9/.evergreen/compile-unix.sh#L147] treating all warnings as errors. The autotools Makefile.am [clears the CFLAGS for zLib|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-c-driver/blob/r1.9/src/mongoc/Makefile.am#L326] to prevent zLib warnings showing up.

We should do something similar in CMake. Currently if we specify
{noformat}
-DCMAKE_C_FLAGS="-Werror"
{noformat}
as a CMake option compile will fail from zLib warnings.

